content: Yes, the pandemic has significantly impacted traffic and commute times in Los Angeles County, as well as other parts of the world. According to a report by INRIX, Los Angeles was ranked among the top cities worldwide for declines in traffic congestion during the pandemic. Overall, the impact of the pandemic on commutes in Los Angeles has been mixed, with some workers shifting to remote work and others returning to the office under new safety protocols. According to some reports, average commute times in Los Angeles have been slightly shorter during the pandemic, but this may also vary depending on specific locations and times of the day.
